; Coverage for amount.cc
; Dividing an amount by a percentage treats the percentage as a fraction:
; $1190 / 19% = $1190 / 0.19 = $6263.16. The "%" commodity triggers
; the special multiply-by-100 logic in the division operator.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $1190.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --format "%(amount / 19%)\n"
$6263.16
$-6263.16
end test
